        <p>Putting together a list of resources (courses, books, training) valuable for learning
			XSLT:<ul id="ul_lbs_bdz_ypb">
			<li>Michael Kay's "<xref
				href="https://www.amazon.com/XSLT-2-0-XPath-Programmers-Reference/dp/0470192747"
				format="html" scope="external">XSLT 2.0 and XPath 2.0</xref>", especially Part I:
				Foundations.</li>
			<li><xref href="https://www.delightfulcomputing.com/xslfaq/xsl/" format="html"
				scope="external">XSLT Frequently Asked Questions</xref> maintained by Dave
				Pauson.</li>
			<li><xref href="https://www.delightfulcomputing.com/" format="html" scope="external"
				>XSLT training courses</xref> by Liam Quinn.</li>
			<li><xref href="http://expertml.com/tom.html" format="html" scope="external">XSLT
				training</xref> by Tomos Hillman.</li>
			<li>An<xref
				href="https://www.udemy.com/course/practical-transformation-using-xslt-and-xpath"
				format="html" scope="external"> Udemy course</xref> by Ken Holman containing also
				some free lectures.</li>
			<li>XSLT Training courses by Dimitre Novatchev on <xref
				href="https://www.pluralsight.com/authors/dimitre-novatchev" format="html"
				scope="external">PluralSight</xref>.</li>
			<li>XSLT consulting by <xref href="http://www.mulberrytech.com/xsl/" format="html"
				scope="external">Mulberry Technologies</xref>.</li>
			<li>Our Oxygen XML <xref href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/partners.html#trainingpartners"
				format="html" scope="external">training partners</xref>. </li>
			</ul></p>
